ared disability, but there is a great deal more we can do.     Share         Disabled People: Recruitment and Retention      The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     David Mackintosh (Northampton South) (Con)       Share       3. What steps the Government are taking to ensure that employers are supported in recruiting and retaining disabled people.   [907333]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Justin Tomlinson (North Swindon) (Con)       Share       15. What steps the Government are taking to ensure that employers are supported in recruiting and retaining disabled people.   [907345]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Sir David Amess (Southend West) (Con)       Share       18. What steps the Government are taking to ensure that employers are supported in recruiting and retaining disabled people.   [907348]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Minister for Disabled People, Health and Work (Penny Mordaunt)       Share       We already support employers through the new Disability Confident scheme, Access to Work and the Fit for Work service. Other measures are planned. The Green Paper consultation will provide further insight into how we can support employers and their disabled employees.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     David Mackintosh       Share       What advice can my hon. Friend offer to people such as my constituent Jehanzaib Sabih, who is deaf, so struggles t